title: For Sale:  Collectible Winchester
postcontent: Winchester model 47 .22 S/L/L.R. single shot bolt action. From 1949 to 1954 Winchester produced the Model 47 rifle. It is an entry level single shot .22 caliber rim fire rifle. The Model 47 single shot possesses two interesting features. Rearward movement of the bolt automatically moves the safety lever to the safe position and it is the only pre-64 bolt-action .22 rifle with a red fire position indicator.It's a bit of a rarity; only manufactured from 1948 to 1954, with 43,123 made.Earlier bolts were straight-handled, later ones used swept-back handles. This one is straight indicating it was an early one. There is no serial number, guns produced before 1968 were not required to have serial numbers. This gun is in it's original condition with good blueing and the stock is in great shape, no cracked wood. FACE TO FACE transaction, NO SHIPPING, price is firm.
